Stores the given information in the response header dictionary of the specified type.
This function handles the following information types: 'lang', 'encoding', 'cache'. They are stored under the 'Accept-Language', 'Accept-Encoding', 'Cache-Control' keys respectively.
The content of the information is read from the user request.
If the specified information type is valid, it should be in the updated response header. If any problem occurs, the function should return the original header dictionary unchanged.

@param info_type The type of information to store in the header.
@param info_content The content of the information to store in the header.
@param header The existing response header dictionary.

@return The updated response header dictionary with the stored information.

